  "text": "Cataglyphis velox ants show increasing bias towards the PI direction as home vector length increases (figure 2a,c) in a manner quantitatively predicted by optimal cue integration based on the decrease in PI directional uncertainty (figure 2c). We examined several alternative models of how the PI state might have affected directional choice (table 1) but none provide as close a fit to the data as the assumption that the cues are weighted inversely to the predicted directional variance of PI. We thus have equivalent evidence of optimal cue combination in ants such as has been provided in many psychophysical studies in humans [CITATION_1] .",
